spec: multiprocessing_extra114
version: ">=3.11"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html — Python multiprocessing module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/context.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends multiprocessing_extra113.zspec.zsdl."
    - "This spec covers: wave 256 theme — multiprocessing Queue, Pipe, Barrier, Event factory method co_qualname and co_varnames.__len__() attributes not covered in extra91-extra113. Prior specs covered: Queue.__code__.co_argcount==2 (extra91), Pipe.__code__.co_argcount==2 (extra91), Queue.__module__=='multiprocessing.context' (extra91), Pipe.__module__=='multiprocessing.context' (extra91), Queue.__qualname__=='BaseContext.Queue' (extra91), Pipe.__qualname__=='BaseContext.Pipe' (extra91), Event.__code__.co_argcount==1 (extra91), Barrier.__code__.co_argcount==4 (extra91). NOT previously covered: Queue/Pipe/Barrier/Event co_qualname values, Queue/Pipe/Barrier/Event co_varnames.__len__(). NEW in extra114: Queue.__code__.co_qualname=='BaseContext.Queue' (len=17); Pipe.__code__.co_qualname=='BaseContext.Pipe' (len=16, shortest); Barrier.__code__.co_qualname=='BaseContext.Barrier' (len=19, longest); Event.__code__.co_qualname=='BaseContext.Event' (len=17, tied with Queue); Queue.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==3; Pipe.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==3 (tied with Queue); Barrier.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==5; Event.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==2 (fewest). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.Queue and Pipe are bound methods of the default BaseContext instance, not standalone functions or classes. Their co_qualname includes the class prefix 'BaseContext.' which is why co_qualname differs from __name__. Queue.__code__.co_qualname=='BaseContext.Queue' (len=17) while Queue.__name__=='Queue' (len=5). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.Barrier.__code__.co_qualname=='BaseContext.Barrier' (len=19, longest in spec). Barrier takes 4 args (self, parties, action, timeout) so co_argcount=4 and co_varnames has 5 entries (4 params + 1 local). multiprocessing.Event.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==2 (self and Event local variable) — fewest co_varnames in spec. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing Queue and Pipe co_qualname — extra114
#
# Wave 256 theme: Queue and Pipe co_qualname values (not previously covered).
#
# multiprocessing.Queue.__code__.co_qualname  == 'BaseContext.Queue'  (len=17)
# multiprocessing.Pipe.__code__.co_qualname   == 'BaseContext.Pipe'   (len=16, shortest)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table multiprocessing_extra114.mp_queue_pipe_coqualname:
  description: "multiprocessing Queue and Pipe co_qualname checks in mpqp114 namespace — wave 256 theme: multiprocessing.Queue and Pipe are bound methods of BaseContext; their co_qualname reflects this with the 'BaseContext.' prefix; multiprocessing.Queue.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__('BaseContext.Queue')==True (len=17: 'BaseContext.'=12+'Queue'=5=17; co_qualname uses the class-qualified form because Queue is defined as a method in the BaseContext class body in Lib/multiprocessing/context.py; compare: Queue.__qualname__=='BaseContext.Queue' which matches co_qualname); multiprocessing.Queue.__code__.co_qualname.__len__()==17; multiprocessing.Queue.__code__.co_name.__eq__('Queue')==True (co_name is the unqualified function name); multiprocessing.Queue.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__(2)==True (self and maxsize; from extra91); multiprocessing.Queue.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==3 ('self','maxsize','Queue': 2 params plus 1 local 'Queue' for the class to instantiate); multiprocessing.Pipe.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__('BaseContext.Pipe')==True (len=16: 'BaseContext.'=12+'Pipe'=4=16; shortest co_qualname in spec); multiprocessing.Pipe.__code__.co_qualname.__len__()==16; multiprocessing.Pipe.__code__.co_name.__eq__('Pipe')==True; multiprocessing.Pipe.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__(2)==True (self and duplex); multiprocessing.Pipe.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==3 ('self','duplex','Pipe': tied with Queue; both have 3 co_varnames); compare co_qualname lengths: Pipe=16 (shortest) < Queue==Event==17 (tied) < Barrier=19 (longest); verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: code_attrs
  id_prefix: mpqp114

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [q_coq_eq,    Queue.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__,   ["BaseContext.Queue"], true, "Queue.__code__.co_qualname == 'BaseContext.Queue' (len=17); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [q_coq_len,   Queue.__code__.co_qualname.__len__,  [],                   17,   "Queue.__code__.co_qualname.__len__() == 17 ('BaseContext.Queue'=17); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [q_co_name,   Queue.__code__.co_name.__eq__,       ["Queue"],            true, "Queue.__code__.co_name == 'Queue' (unqualified name); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [q_argc,      Queue.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__,   [2],                  true, "Queue.__code__.co_argcount == 2 (self and maxsize); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [q_var_len,   Queue.__code__.co_varnames.__len__,  [],                   3,    "Queue.__code__.co_varnames.__len__() == 3 ('self','maxsize','Queue'); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [p_coq_eq,    Pipe.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__,    ["BaseContext.Pipe"],  true, "Pipe.__code__.co_qualname == 'BaseContext.Pipe' (len=16, shortest in spec); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [p_coq_len,   Pipe.__code__.co_qualname.__len__,   [],                   16,   "Pipe.__code__.co_qualname.__len__() == 16 ('BaseContext.Pipe'=16, shortest); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [p_co_name,   Pipe.__code__.co_name.__eq__,        ["Pipe"],             true, "Pipe.__code__.co_name == 'Pipe' (unqualified name); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [p_argc,      Pipe.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__,    [2],                  true, "Pipe.__code__.co_argcount == 2 (self and duplex); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [p_var_len,   Pipe.__code__.co_varnames.__len__,   [],                   3,    "Pipe.__code__.co_varnames.__len__() == 3 (tied with Queue: 'self','duplex','Pipe'); verified with Python 3.14.3"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing Barrier and Event co_qualname — extra114
#
# Wave 256 theme: Barrier and Event co_qualname values (not previously covered).
#
# multiprocessing.Barrier.__code__.co_qualname  == 'BaseContext.Barrier'  (len=19, longest)
# multiprocessing.Event.__code__.co_qualname    == 'BaseContext.Event'    (len=17, tied with Queue)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table multiprocessing_extra114.mp_barrier_event_coqualname:
  description: "multiprocessing Barrier and Event co_qualname checks in mpqp114 namespace — wave 256 theme: multiprocessing.Barrier.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__('BaseContext.Barrier')==True (len=19: 'BaseContext.'=12+'Barrier'=7=19; this is the longest co_qualname in spec — 'Barrier'=7 chars is the longest factory method name; Barrier.__code__.co_argcount==4 from extra91: self, parties, action, timeout; Barrier creates a synchronization barrier for a fixed number of processes); multiprocessing.Barrier.__code__.co_qualname.__len__()==19; multiprocessing.Barrier.__code__.co_name.__eq__('Barrier')==True; multiprocessing.Barrier.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==5 (4 params plus 1 local: 'self','parties','action','timeout','Barrier'; the local 'Barrier' variable is the class to instantiate); multiprocessing.Event.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__('BaseContext.Event')==True (len=17: 'BaseContext.'=12+'Event'=5=17; tied with Queue co_qualname len=17; Event creates a process-safe event for signaling between processes); multiprocessing.Event.__code__.co_qualname.__len__()==17; multiprocessing.Event.__code__.co_name.__eq__('Event')==True; multiprocessing.Event.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__(1)==True (self only: from extra91); multiprocessing.Event.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==2 ('self','Event': fewest co_varnames in spec — Event takes no factory arguments, just self, plus 1 local for the class); compare co_qualname lengths: Pipe=16 (shortest) < Queue==Event==17 (tied) < Barrier=19 (longest, difference of 3 from Pipe); compare co_varnames lengths: Event=2 (fewest) < Queue==Pipe==3 (tied) < Barrier=5 (most); verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: code_attrs
  id_prefix: mpqp114a

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [b_coq_eq,    Barrier.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__,   ["BaseContext.Barrier"], true, "Barrier.__code__.co_qualname == 'BaseContext.Barrier' (len=19, longest in spec); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [b_coq_len,   Barrier.__code__.co_qualname.__len__,  [],                     19,   "Barrier.__code__.co_qualname.__len__() == 19 ('BaseContext.Barrier'=19, longest); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [b_co_name,   Barrier.__code__.co_name.__eq__,       ["Barrier"],            true, "Barrier.__code__.co_name == 'Barrier' (unqualified name, len=7); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [b_argc,      Barrier.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__,   [4],                    true, "Barrier.__code__.co_argcount == 4 (self, parties, action, timeout); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [b_var_len,   Barrier.__code__.co_varnames.__len__,  [],                     5,    "Barrier.__code__.co_varnames.__len__() == 5 (4 params + 1 local 'Barrier' class var; most in spec); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [e_coq_eq,    Event.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__,     ["BaseContext.Event"],  true, "Event.__code__.co_qualname == 'BaseContext.Event' (len=17, tied with Queue); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [e_coq_len,   Event.__code__.co_qualname.__len__,    [],                     17,   "Event.__code__.co_qualname.__len__() == 17 (tied with Queue co_qualname len=17); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [e_co_name,   Event.__code__.co_name.__eq__,         ["Event"],              true, "Event.__code__.co_name == 'Event' (unqualified name, len=5); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [e_argc,      Event.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__,     [1],                    true, "Event.__code__.co_argcount == 1 (self only); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [e_var_len,   Event.__code__.co_varnames.__len__,    [],                     2,    "Event.__code__.co_varnames.__len__() == 2 ('self','Event'; fewest co_varnames in spec); verified with Python 3.14.3"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing factory method module and name identity — extra114
#
# Wave 256 theme: Queue, Pipe, Barrier, Event __name__ and __module__ lengths.
#
# All four share __module__ == 'multiprocessing.context' (len=23)
# Queue.__name__ len=5, Pipe.__name__ len=4, Barrier.__name__ len=7, Event.__name__ len=5
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table multiprocessing_extra114.mp_factory_module_names:
  description: "multiprocessing factory method module and name identity checks in mpqp114 namespace — wave 256 theme: all four factory methods (Queue, Pipe, Barrier, Event) share the same __module__ 'multiprocessing.context' (len=23) because they are all bound methods of the BaseContext class defined in Lib/multiprocessing/context.py; multiprocessing.Queue.__module__.__eq__('multiprocessing.context')==True (len=23); multiprocessing.Pipe.__module__.__eq__('multiprocessing.context')==True; multiprocessing.Barrier.__module__.__eq__('multiprocessing.context')==True; multiprocessing.Event.__module__.__eq__('multiprocessing.context')==True; compare __name__ lengths: Pipe=4 (shortest) < Queue==Event==5 (tied) < Barrier=7 (longest; 'Barrier'=7 chars is longest factory method name); multiprocessing.Queue.__name__.__len__()==5 (from extra91; __name__=='Queue'); multiprocessing.Pipe.__name__.__len__()==4 (from extra91; __name__=='Pipe', shortest); multiprocessing.Barrier.__name__.__len__()==7 (longest __name__ in spec; 'Barrier'=7); multiprocessing.Event.__name__.__len__()==5 (tied with Queue); note: __name__ lengths match the method name lengths in co_qualname: co_qualname len - 12 ('BaseContext.'=12) = __name__ len; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: mpqp114b

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [q_mod_eq,    Queue.__module__.__eq__,    ["multiprocessing.context"], true, "Queue.__module__ == 'multiprocessing.context' (len=23); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [q_mod_len,   Queue.__module__.__len__,   [],                         23,   "Queue.__module__.__len__() == 23 ('multiprocessing.context'=23); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [p_mod_eq,    Pipe.__module__.__eq__,     ["multiprocessing.context"], true, "Pipe.__module__ == 'multiprocessing.context' (same module as Queue); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [b_mod_eq,    Barrier.__module__.__eq__,  ["multiprocessing.context"], true, "Barrier.__module__ == 'multiprocessing.context'; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [e_mod_eq,    Event.__module__.__eq__,    ["multiprocessing.context"], true, "Event.__module__ == 'multiprocessing.context'; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [q_name_len,  Queue.__name__.__len__,     [],                         5,    "Queue.__name__.__len__() == 5 ('Queue'=5); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [p_name_len,  Pipe.__name__.__len__,      [],                         4,    "Pipe.__name__.__len__() == 4 ('Pipe'=4, shortest name in spec); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [b_name_len,  Barrier.__name__.__len__,   [],                         7,    "Barrier.__name__.__len__() == 7 ('Barrier'=7, longest name in spec); verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [e_name_len,  Event.__name__.__len__,     [],                         5,    "Event.__name__.__len__() == 5 ('Event'=5, tied with Queue); verified with Python 3.14.3"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Standalone invariants — extra114
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant multiprocessing_extra114.Queue_co_qualname_len_17:
  description: "multiprocessing.Queue.__code__.co_qualname.__len__() == 17 — 'BaseContext.Queue' = 'BaseContext.'=12 + 'Queue'=5 = 17; multiprocessing.Queue is a bound method of BaseContext so co_qualname carries the class prefix; multiprocessing.Queue.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__('BaseContext.Queue')==True; co_qualname matches Queue.__qualname__ (both are 'BaseContext.Queue'); multiprocessing.Queue.__code__.co_argcount==2 (self and maxsize); multiprocessing.Queue.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==3 ('self','maxsize','Queue'); multiprocessing.Queue.__module__=='multiprocessing.context' (len=23); compare co_qualname lengths: Pipe=16 (1 shorter than Queue=17) < Queue==Event==17 (tied) < Barrier=19 (2 longer than Queue=17); first standalone Queue co_qualname length invariant in mpqp114 namespace; wave 256; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  category: code_attrs
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Queue.__code__.co_qualname.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 17

invariant multiprocessing_extra114.Pipe_co_qualname_len_16:
  description: "multiprocessing.Pipe.__code__.co_qualname.__len__() == 16 — 'BaseContext.Pipe' = 'BaseContext.'=12 + 'Pipe'=4 = 16; this is the shortest co_qualname in this spec; multiprocessing.Pipe.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__('BaseContext.Pipe')==True; co_qualname matches Pipe.__qualname__; multiprocessing.Pipe.__code__.co_argcount==2 (self and duplex); multiprocessing.Pipe.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==3 (tied with Queue); multiprocessing.Pipe.__module__=='multiprocessing.context' (len=23); compare: Pipe co_qualname len=16 (shortest; 'Pipe'=4 chars) < Queue==Event==17 < Barrier=19 (longest; 'Barrier'=7 chars); Pipe creates a pair of connection objects for two-way communication between processes; first standalone Pipe co_qualname length invariant in mpqp114 namespace; wave 256; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  category: code_attrs
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Pipe.__code__.co_qualname.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 16

invariant multiprocessing_extra114.Barrier_co_qualname_len_19:
  description: "multiprocessing.Barrier.__code__.co_qualname.__len__() == 19 — 'BaseContext.Barrier' = 'BaseContext.'=12 + 'Barrier'=7 = 19; this is the longest co_qualname in this spec; multiprocessing.Barrier.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__('BaseContext.Barrier')==True; co_qualname matches Barrier.__qualname__; multiprocessing.Barrier.__code__.co_argcount==4 (self, parties, action, timeout — most args in spec); multiprocessing.Barrier.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==5 (most co_varnames in spec: 4 params + 1 local); multiprocessing.Barrier.__module__=='multiprocessing.context' (len=23); compare co_qualname lengths: Pipe=16 < Queue==Event==17 < Barrier=19 (longest; 'Barrier'=7 is longest factory method name in spec); first standalone Barrier co_qualname length invariant in mpqp114 namespace; wave 256; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  category: code_attrs
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Barrier.__code__.co_qualname.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 19

invariant multiprocessing_extra114.Event_co_varnames_len_2:
  description: "multiprocessing.Event.__code__.co_varnames.__len__() == 2 — co_varnames==('self','Event'): 1 parameter (self) plus 1 local variable ('Event' for the class to instantiate); this is the fewest co_varnames of any factory method in this spec; multiprocessing.Event.__code__.co_argcount==1 (self only; Event takes no factory arguments from the caller); multiprocessing.Event.__code__.co_qualname=='BaseContext.Event' (len=17); multiprocessing.Event.__module__=='multiprocessing.context' (len=23); compare co_varnames lengths: Event=2 (fewest) < Queue==Pipe==3 (tied) < Barrier=5 (most); Event has the simplest implementation of the four factory methods: it takes only self and delegates to the implementation class; first standalone Event co_varnames length invariant in mpqp114 namespace; wave 256; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  category: code_attrs
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Event.__code__.co_varnames.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 2

invariant multiprocessing_extra114.Barrier_co_varnames_len_5:
  description: "multiprocessing.Barrier.__code__.co_varnames.__len__() == 5 — co_varnames==('self','parties','action','timeout','Barrier'): 4 parameters (self, parties, action, timeout) plus 1 local variable ('Barrier' for the class to instantiate); this is the most co_varnames of any factory method in this spec; multiprocessing.Barrier.__code__.co_argcount==4 (most positional args in spec); multiprocessing.Barrier.__code__.co_qualname=='BaseContext.Barrier' (len=19, longest in spec); multiprocessing.Barrier.__module__=='multiprocessing.context' (len=23); compare co_varnames: Event=2 (fewest) < Queue==Pipe==3 (tied) < Barrier=5 (most; 'parties','action','timeout' give it 3 more than Event); Barrier creates a synchronization barrier for a fixed number of processes (parties); once parties processes have called wait(), they are all released simultaneously; first standalone Barrier co_varnames length invariant in mpqp114 namespace; wave 256; verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  category: code_attrs
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Barrier.__code__.co_varnames.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 5

